# tetsum

A simple static C++ library demonstrating Conan 2 packaging with CMake.

## Overview

This library provides a trivial `sum` function. It demonstrates:
- CMake-based static library structure
- Conan 2 packaging
- Unit testing with GoogleTest (as test_requires)

## API

```cpp
#include <tetsum/tetsum.hpp>

int result = tetsum::sum(2, 3);  // Returns 5
```

## Project Structure

```
tetsum/
├── conanfile.py       # Conan 2 recipe
├── CMakeLists.txt     # CMake configuration
├── Config.cmake.in    # CMake package config template
├── include/
│   └── tetsum/
│       └── tetsum.hpp # Public API
├── src/
│   └── tetsum.cpp     # Implementation
└── tests/
    ├── CMakeLists.txt
    └── tetsum_test.cpp
```

## Build Options

| Option | Default | Description |
|--------|---------|-------------|
| `build_tests` | `False` | Build unit tests |
| `run_tests` | `False` | Run tests after build |

## Quick Start

### Build and install to local cache

```bash
conan create . --build=missing
```

### Build with tests

```bash
conan create . -o build_tests=True -o run_tests=True --build=missing
```

### Local development

```bash
conan install . -o build_tests=True --build=missing
cmake --preset conan-default
cmake --build --preset conan-release
ctest --preset conan-release --output-on-failure
```

## Consuming the Library

```cmake
find_package(tetsum CONFIG REQUIRED)
target_link_libraries(your_target PRIVATE tetsum::tetsum)
```

